      • createView

        org.eclipse.emf.cdo.view.CDOView createView(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.branch.CDOBranch branch,
                                            long timestamp,
                                            boolean shouldInvalidate)
        Creates a non-audit CDO view on a specified branch with the given branch point. If clients should configure shouldInvalidate as false if CDO invalidation events are to be ignored.
        Parameters:
        branch - the CDO branch.
        timeStamp - the timestamp for the branch point.
        shouldInvalidate - false if invalidation events to be ignored. Otherwise false.
        Returns:
        the non-audit CDO view.

      • createTransaction

        org.eclipse.emf.cdo.transaction.CDOTransaction createTransaction(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.branch.CDOBranch branch)
        Creates a audit CDO view for the specified branch. The HEAD of the transaction will be unspecified.

        NOTE: the CDO revision cache will use weak references.

        Parameters:
        branch - the branch where the transaction has to be opened.
        Returns:
        the clean audit CDO view instance.

      • getBranch

        org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.branch.CDOBranch getBranch(IBranchPath branchPath)
        Returns the most recently created branch with the specified its branch path. The main branch is returned for the fixed branch name CDOBranch.MAIN_BRANCH_NAME.
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the path of the branch to retrieve.
        Returns:
        the most recent branch with the specified path, or null if no such branch could be found.

      • getOldestBranch

        org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.branch.CDOBranch getOldestBranch(IBranchPath branchPath)
        Returns with branch which is associated with the branch path argument.

        Multiple CDO branch with identical name but different ID could be associated with a single branch path (due to task context synchronization). This will return with the very first (oldest) branch.

        Parameters:
        branchPath - the path of the branch to retrieve.
        Returns:
        the oldest branch associated with the branch path argument.
